✔ Do’s
Maintain a professional profile – Keep your posts respectful and appropriate.
Protect your privacy – Use strong passwords and privacy settings.
Verify information before sharing – Avoid spreading false or misleading content.
Engage positively – Communicate politely and respectfully with others.
Use social media for learning – Follow educational pages and skill-based content.

❌ Don’ts
Do not share personal information – Avoid posting phone number, address, or sensitive details.
Do not post inappropriate content – It can harm your reputation.
Avoid cyberbullying or negative comments – Be respectful online.
Do not click on suspicious links – It may lead to scams or malware.
Avoid oversharing – Posting too much personal content can be risky.
